\section{FTBS}
\label{sec:orgba6d87c}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./FTBS-r-c.png}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./FTBS-r-d.png}
\end{center}

\begin{itemize}
\item To make this stable I needed a \(delta_t\) of 0.001 to make this stable.
\item Clearly diffuses in the cross stream direction.
\item The maximum diffuses quickly (exponentially).
\item The pulse slouches backwards in the along stream direction.
\item The error increases linearly.
\item It seems to conserve total U pretty well.
\end{itemize}

\section{AB3}
\label{sec:org084104a}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./AB3-r-c.png}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./AB3-r-d.png}
\end{center}

\begin{itemize}
\item To make this stable I needed a \(delta_t\) of 0.00075 to make this stable. So clearly a smaller than FTBS.
\item Doesn't diffuse much in the cross stream direction.
\item Moves forward a tiny bit in the along stream direction.
\item Does a great job at retaining the maximum.
\item Error grows slower.
\item Conserves total U very well.
\end{itemize}


\section{square}
\label{sec:orgd6f7dc9}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./FTBS-s-c.png}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./FTBS-s-d.png}
\end{center}

\begin{itemize}
\item Immediately becomes very non square and diffuses super fast in both directions
\item The maximum u value decreases very fast
\item The error is larger than total U by the end of 10 cycles
\end{itemize}


\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./Ab3-s-c.png}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[width=.9\linewidth]{./AB3-s-d.png}
\end{center}

\begin{itemize}
\item CRAZY!!!
\item Immediately becomes super funky.
\item Alot of small scale noise almost like an aliasing error
\item The maximum U is oddly discontinuous
\item The minimum U goes below 0 which it doesn't do in any of ther other runs
\item Error eclipses integrated U pretty quickly
\end{itemize}
